                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d420">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">352.3715/30: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-03-05T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 5, 1937—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>116. At request of Cuban Government we are giving consideration to possibility of
                    evacuation of 200 Cubans from Valencia to Marseille by American naval vessel. We
                    understand from Cuban Embassy in Madrid that arrangements have been made with
                    French Government for admission these Cuban refugees into France, but before
                    taking action we wish confirmation by telegraph that French authorities would be
                    agreeable to entry of these Cubans.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
